==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ochre
<hw>O"chre</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>ocre</ets>, L. <ets>ochra</ets>, fr. Gr.
<?/, from (<?/) pale, pale yellow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A impure earthy ore of iron or a ferruginous clay,
usually red (hematite) or yellow (limonite), -- used as a pigment in
making paints, etc. The name is also applied to clays of other
colors.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A metallic oxide occurring in earthy
form; <as>as, tungstic <ex>ocher</ex> or tungstite</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The color of ocher{1}, varying around orange, from
more yellowish to more reddish in tint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ocher mutation</ent>⟦br⟧

